  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>Ultra-light Mesh network node (Zigbee)</p>]]></text></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>Long-range LoRa radio module</p>]]></text></answer>
</question>

<!-- ===================== LECTURE 2 (10 questions) ===================== -->

<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>W2-01: IoT Triangle</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>An engineer designing an IoT network must choose a compromise – they can optimize only <b>two of three</b> parameters simultaneously. What are these parameters?</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <defaultgrade>1</defaultgrade>
  <penalty>0.3333333</penalty>
  <single>true</single>
  <shuffleanswers>true</shuffleanswers>
  <answer fraction="100" format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>Range, Throughput, Battery life</p>]]></text></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>Price, Quality, Delivery time</p>]]></text></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>Computing power, RAM, Disk capacity</p>]]></text></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>Bandwidth, Latency, Security</p>]]></text></answer>
</question>

<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>W2-02: Wi-Fi in IoT</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>Why is Wi-Fi a <b>poor</b> choice for autonomous battery-powered IoT sensors?</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <defaultgrade>1</defaultgrade>
  <penalty>0.3333333</penalty>
  <single>true</single>
  <shuffleanswers>true</shuffleanswers>
  <answer fraction="100" format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>It is very power-hungry – the network scanning and connection handshake process consumes hundreds of mA</p>]]></text></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>It does not support IP protocol</p>]]></text></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>It has too large range (over 50 km)</p>]]></text></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>It requires licensed radio spectrum</p>]]></text></answer>
</question>

<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>W2-03: BLE</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>How does Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) differ from classic Bluetooth?</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <defaultgrade>1</defaultgrade>
  <penalty>0.3333333</penalty>
  <single>true</single>
  <shuffleanswers>true</shuffleanswers>
  <answer fraction="100" format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>BLE puts the radio to sleep immediately after sending a packet, drastically reducing power consumption</p>]]></text></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>BLE has a range above 10 km</p>]]></text></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>BLE streams Hi-Fi audio</p>]]></text></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>BLE requires constant 230 V mains power</p>]]></text></answer>
</question>

<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>W2-04: Zigbee Mesh</text></name>
